==English==
{{wikipediapar|Chaldeans}}

===Etymology===
From Greek χαλδαιος "astrologer" (Herodotus 3.155), χαλδαικος "of [[Chaldaea|Χαλδαια]]".

===Adjective ===
'''Chaldean'''
*pertaining to [[Chaldea]], or ancient [[Babylonia]] in general, as in 'Chaldean mythology' (synonymous to 'Mesopotamian mythology'). 

===Noun===
'''Chaldean'''
#a native of [[Chaldea]], the [[Chaldees]] of the King James Version of the Bible, translating Hebrew כשדים.
#a member of the Chaldean Catholic Church, a uniate church of the Roman Catholic Church
# the [[Khaldi]], an ancient people of the Caucasus; in older references also used synonymously with [[Urartian]]
#(''Bible'') a [[diviner]] or [[astrologer]]

